  "text": ") and a low Arrhenius activation energy (E a = 3.7 kcal\u00b7 mol \u22121 ) [CITATION_1] . This corresponds to a water transport rate of about 3 \u00d7 10 9 water molecules/monomer/s. This exceptionally high water transport capability and sharp water selectivity of AqpZ make AqpZ-embedded polymer membranes (polymersomes, planar membranes) an ideal tool in developing reverse osmosis (RO) membranes with a low energy cost. ",
